This paper is about the extraction and analysis of character networks from works of fiction, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of character networks for information retrieval and recommendation systems, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper discusses the descriptive tools used to characterize character networks, which could be related to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also mentions the limitations of existing approaches and the need for further research, which could be related to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
